reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not worth it. Back pain and loud.
reviews.reviewText: I wish I had just spent the extra like 40 for a different mattress. I tried giving it time to see if I’d like it but still really don’t. For 1. It’s so loud? Like a simple move and you hear them springs going off. It’s actually irritating. Careful doing too much in bed if you get this. I feel like I can’t move. 2. It’s not that comfortable tbh. I will never buy another spring bed again after this one (and I grew up on mattresses like this) it makes my back hurt and I’ve never had an issue with beds with similar firmness but now my shoulders and back hurt almost daily. Only thing in my life that’s changed is the mattress.Not much value for money. If you’re in a tight spot it’s good for short term but I honestly just wish I splurged a bit more. As far as set up it was a little bit annoying but not terrible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars It's good enough for the guest room ....
reviews.reviewText: So I was quite excited getting a hybrid mattress as this would be my first one. My others have all been spring OR memory.When I first rolled out the mattress, there was a very significant height difference from the left side of the mattress to the right side. There was a deep slope that went down on the right side, and I was afraid the mattress would never even out. THANKFULLY, the mattress did even out after 2 weeks. Before it evened out, I asked my friend to sleep on the left side (as this seemed the more comfortable choice) and I was quite embarrassed by this. She was a good sport, though. I think the trick was to lay on it from time to time as days went by to get the springs to spring all the way up eventually. I think I did hear some "boing" sounds; as if the springs were finally bouncing up in the right side. It did not rise to 10 inches. Mine only went up 8.75 inches like so many others in the review.It's nothing fancy, but it's definitely good enough for my guest room. It's a firm mattress so I did get a medium poofy topper for it so it wasn't so firm. I'm just glad the whole thing evened out, otherwise I was going to donate it.
